    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"280178\">Tim Hosgood</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/241590-theory.3A-algebraic-topology-.26-homological-algebra/topic/.C4.8Cech.20cohomology.20.26.20sheaf.20cohomology/near/282891984\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I’m very out of practice with this sort of stuff, but I also don’t think the colimit is zero, and I think you could cook up some counterexample showing this on something like the Sierpinski space</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I will look that that... though I have no idea about Siepinski spaces tbh :)</p>",
